I prefer Skyshine as well I hate Giants ~  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#112512><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub16.ezboard.com/bdruzzilro86846.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=amueldaemon>Amuel Daemon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Newbie</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#CCCCC8>(11/4/01 1:03:35 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ..</span><hr size=1> It really depends.<br>
<br>
If you are a hardcore player that plays 3+ hours a day (at the least), then it doesn't really matter that much.  You can switch faction fairly easily.  <br>
<br>
Most hardcore would go giant simply because it is harder to do fun raids and keep good dragon faction at the same time then it is to do the opposite.  If you are on giant faction and get a dragon faction quest item, or vice versa, it is very possible to switch factions then switch back.<br>
<br>
If you don't play 3+ hours everyday or you are in a small guild, then dragon faction would be better.  It is easier to get SS quest pieces then it is to get Kael quest pieces.  Also, while factioning in Kael you can also get dwarf quest pieces.  You can still kill some dragon faction mobs as long as you don't over do it (my guild regularly killed dragons in WW for Dragon's Bane quest for a month+ three times a day and most of us still managed to keep decent faction).<br>
<br>
My guild (Hoss) does NToV, Lendi, Yel, etc and most members can still keep their dragon faction up.  Some of us don't really care that much anymore and are just on dorf faction =)<br>
<br>
As far as the quality of armors go, Kael has more AC but less stats (in most cases), SS has less ac but more stats (again in most cases), and Thurg is not as good as either in either way.<br>
<br>
Hope I didn't ramble too much.<br>
